\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {31}{\ignorespaces Generation~IV agent frameworks versus modern operating systems (Linux/Windows~NT). Codex's sub-agent spawning maps to \texttt  {fork()}; its sandbox maps to \texttt  {chroot}/container isolation; Claude Code's hooks parallel Linux Security Module (LSM) hooks; and the approval gate corresponds to \texttt  {sudo} privilege elevation. The key advance: confronting real-world codebases with irreversible side effects demands formal isolation and human-in-the-loop approval.}}{63}{figure.caption.119}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ae:gen4}{{31}{63}{Generation~IV agent frameworks versus modern operating systems (Linux/Windows~NT). Codex's sub-agent spawning maps to \texttt {fork()}; its sandbox maps to \texttt {chroot}/container isolation; Claude Code's hooks parallel Linux Security Module (LSM) hooks; and the approval gate corresponds to \texttt {sudo} privilege elevation. The key advance: confronting real-world codebases with irreversible side effects demands formal isolation and human-in-the-loop approval}{figure.caption.119}{}}
