\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {46}{\ignorespaces Predicted three-layer Fabless-AI industry structure (right) and its semiconductor analog (left). Fabless model designers (the future ARM/Qualcomm of AI) design architectures and weights without owning compute. AI foundries (TSMC/Samsung plus hyperscale cloud) manufacture dedicated inference chips and provide large-scale training. OS-layer gateways (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini) control the user interface and capture disproportionate value--- replaying the Microsoft-versus-Intel dynamic of the PC era, where the OS gateway captured more value than the chip manufacturer. The fundamental driver: copyability of weights eliminates the physical moat at the model layer, pushing value to the silicon (L1) and the gateway (L5).}}{91}{figure.caption.147}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:social:fabless_ai}{{46}{91}{Predicted three-layer Fabless-AI industry structure (right) and its semiconductor analog (left). Fabless model designers (the future ARM/Qualcomm of AI) design architectures and weights without owning compute. AI foundries (TSMC/Samsung plus hyperscale cloud) manufacture dedicated inference chips and provide large-scale training. OS-layer gateways (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini) control the user interface and capture disproportionate value--- replaying the Microsoft-versus-Intel dynamic of the PC era, where the OS gateway captured more value than the chip manufacturer. The fundamental driver: copyability of weights eliminates the physical moat at the model layer, pushing value to the silicon (L1) and the gateway (L5)}{figure.caption.147}{}}
