\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {53}{\ignorespaces Four sequential governance gates applied to every memory block entering the L3 context layer. Gate~1 decides whether information should be persisted or scoped to the current session. Gate~2 assigns a Time-To-Live annotation balancing EU AI Act retention requirements against GDPR's Right to Be Forgotten. Gate~3 enforces reference-counted deletion: physical removal requires all referencing agents to consent. Gate~4 tests whether summaries could leak sensitive attributes, triggering cascading deletion, access isolation, and encrypted storage if necessary. These four gates are the semantic analog of OS page-protection bits.}}{105}{figure.caption.174}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:ethics:privacy}{{53}{105}{Four sequential governance gates applied to every memory block entering the L3 context layer. Gate~1 decides whether information should be persisted or scoped to the current session. Gate~2 assigns a Time-To-Live annotation balancing EU AI Act retention requirements against GDPR's Right to Be Forgotten. Gate~3 enforces reference-counted deletion: physical removal requires all referencing agents to consent. Gate~4 tests whether summaries could leak sensitive attributes, triggering cascading deletion, access isolation, and encrypted storage if necessary. These four gates are the semantic analog of OS page-protection bits}{figure.caption.174}{}}
